    "Then, we explore various approaches found in the literature and categorize them from two distinct perspectives: 1) categorization based on features, and 2) categorization based on algorithms.",
    "In the literature, various definitions can be found for the problem of disinformation detection (Phan et al. 2023; Shu et al. 2017), characterized by distinctions in the type of disinformation (fake news, rumors, hoaxes, etc) and the datasets used.",
    "Some datasets are binary, such as FaKeNewsNet, which labels news articles as fake or real.",
    "Others are multiclass, such as LIAR, which assigns six levels of veracity to statements: true, mostly-true, halftrue, barely-true, false, and pants-fire.",
    "More datasets are discussed in section 6."
